President Obama has nominated Judge Danny C. Reeves to serve on the United States Sentencing Commission. Judge Reeves is currently a United States District Judge for the Eastern District of Kentucky, a position he has held since 2001. Prior to his appointment to the bench, Judge Reeves practiced civil litigation at Bingham Greenebaum Doll LLP. He began his legal career as a law clerk to Judge Eugene E. Siler, Jr. and received his J.D. from Salmon P. Chase College of Law, Northern Kentucky University in 1981.